reviewText: It reminded me of Reality TV: no story line, no plot and not enjoyable.
A funny romp with madcap British humor. Give it a chance.
Not funny at all, pretty depressing. The funny scenes you see in the preview are mysteriously not present in the movie itself. I'd pass on this one, save yourself some money.
I don't like to make negative criticisms of people's creative efforts, so I'll just say I was only able to tolerate a few minutes of this movie.

Entertaining but not worthy of 5 stars I believe.  Filming style reminds me of "Best of Show" and "Spinal Tap".  Overall, it was a good film with a great cast (excluding the Russian choreographer who wasn't funny at all) and the story was understandable.  I like the ending although somewhat predicable, but that's not always a bad thing.
Awesome :) Great comedy, laughed a lot. Characters are very developed and seem real, love the weeding organizer. Want one
This was actually a hidden gem with a lot of funny parts shown in the trailer but with seeing the whole scene in the movie it was great.
This movie is hilarious!  I laughed I laughed so much I cried!  Lucy Punch is awesome I love her in this film.  What a great comedy!

I thought this movie was hilarious and just all around quirky and fun. The actors are what really made it for me. I don't think anyone else could of pulled this script off. My copy arrived early and in fantastic condition! Very happy.
This was a funny movie. I really enjoyed it. Honest, funny and original.
LOVE Lucy Punch! She is great (as usual) in this film.
Great product, accurate & clear product description, fast & excellent service & communication
Dry wit with some cute scenes but not a wow movie.
A light comedy and I like Lucy Punch, she is great, funny and I watched any movie she is in.

Okay, maybe you know how it's going to end.  However,  it's verrrry funny getting there, without the same old tired gimmicks in American rom-coms.  Hilarious and sweet movie. (Much better than 'Bridesmaids'!!)
This was too much like an home made video.  None of the character was particularly likable and it ran like a 'stream of consciousness' book.  Hard to follow.
